Part 4 – Return Values and Responses

All public functions must return a response:

(ok value) → success

(err value) → failure

Example:

(define-public (withdraw (amount uint))
  (if (>= (stx-get-balance tx-sender) amount)
      (ok amount)
      (err u401)))


This makes error handling explicit and auditable, unlike Solidity’s silent reverts.
